OL,3,CBirmingham bin driver forced out of
OL,4,Cjob weeks before Christmas
OL,6,FHe says "I would have carried on until
OL,7,FI was 67," he said. "I didn't want to
OL,8,Fleave. It was a really good job."
OL,10,FInstead of heading out on his usual
OL,11,Fround, George spent his final day
OL,12,Femployed by the council on a picket
OL,13,Fline, standing alongside colleagues
OL,14,Ftaking part in industrial action.
OL,16,F"I'm sad at being forced out just
OL,17,Fbefore Christmas," he said.
OL,19,F"It's not what anybody wants this time
OL,20,Fof year. I enjoyed the camaraderie and
OL,21,Fmeeting people on the streets."
